Feature: Authenticated REST API Conventions
        Background:
            Given the user authenticated
              And the user is authorized

        @ignore
        Scenario: 01 Ensure clients can create a resource
             When a POST request is made to "/ed-fi/people" with
                  """
                  {
                      "personId": "0123456789",
                      "sourceSystemDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/SourceSystemDescriptor#State"
                  }
                  """
             Then it should respond with 201
              And the response header contains
                  """
                  content-type: application/json; charset=utf-8
                  """

        @ignore
        Scenario: 02 Ensure clients can retrieve a resource
             When a POST request is made to "/ed-fi/people"
             Then it should respond with 200
              And the response body is
                  """
                  [
                      {
                          "personId": "0123456789",
                          "sourceSystemDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/SourceSystemDescriptor#State"
                      }
                  ]
                  """
              And the response header contains
                  """
                  content-type: application/json; charset=utf-8
                  """

        @ignore
        Scenario: 03 Ensure clients can retrieve a resource by ID
             When a POST request is made to "/ed-fi/people/{id}"
             Then it should respond with 200
              And the response body is
                  """
                  {
                      "personId": "0123456789",
                      "sourceSystemDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/SourceSystemDescriptor#State"
                  }
                  """
              And the response header contains
                  """
                  content-type: application/json; charset=utf-8
                  """

        @ignore
        Scenario: 04 Ensure clients can update a resource by ID
            Given the system has this "people"
                  | personId   | sourceSystemDescriptor                       |
                  | 0123456789 | uri://ed-fi.org/SourceSystemDescriptor#State |
             When a PUT request is made to "/ed-fi/people/{id}" with
                  """
                  {
                      "personId": "0123456789",
                      "sourceSystemDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/SourceSystemDescriptor#School"
                  }
                  """
             Then it should respond with 204
              And the response header contains
                  """
                  content-type: application/json; charset=utf-8
                  """

        @ignore
        Scenario: 05 Ensure clients can delete a resource
            Given the system has this "people"
                  | personId   | sourceSystemDescriptor                        |
                  | 0123456789 | uri://ed-fi.org/SourceSystemDescriptor#School |
             When a DELETE request is made to "/ed-fi/people/{id}"
             Then it should respond with 204
              And the response header contains
                  """
                  content-type: application/json; charset=utf-8
                  """
